<h2><i class="fa fa-floppy-o"></i> Install</h2>
<p>Start with a base system: fresh Ubuntu 14.04 or 15.x installation with at least 2GB of RAM and 40GB available disk space.</p>
<p>Open a terminal window. Paste into terminal window...</p>

<pre>sudo apt-get install -y git
git clone https://github.com/EnginesOS/EnginesInstaller
cd EnginesInstaller
sudo  ./install_engines.sh alpha</pre>

<p>This will:
  <ul>
    <li>Make sure that git is installed.</li>
    <li>Use git to extract the installer software into a new EnginesInstaller directory.</li>
    <li>Go to the EnginesInstaller directory.</li>
    <li>Install Engines in the /opt/engines directory.</li>
  </ul>
</p>

<p>Follow prompts. Once the installer has run you will be presented with a URL that you will need to open in a browser. Sign in to Engines.</p>
<pre>Username 'admin', password 'password'</pre>
<p>Complete the setup wizard and you're done.</p>
<p>More detailed and technical installation instructions on the <%= link_to (content_tag(:i, nil, class: 'fa fa-git') + " GitHub page"), "https://github.com/EnginesOS/System/wiki/Installation", class: 'btn btn-default btn-lg' %></p>

<h3><i class="fa fa-trash-o"></i> Uninstall</h3>
<p>Open a terminal window (ensuring that you are in the same directory that you used when starting installation) and enter...</p>
<pre>sudo EnginesInstaller/obliterate_engines_no_warning.sh</pre>

